      "acceptanceCriteria": "Ansys Mechanical and FDA in-house FEA code are validated commercial/regulated tools with documented version control and QA procedures; achieved level must meet or exceed required.",
      "rationale": "All three FEA codes (Ansys Mechanical 2022 R2, FDA in-house code, DePuy Synthes internal tool) operate under ISO 9001-compliant QMS environments with documented version control, regression test suites, and change-control logs. Required level 2 is met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Benchmark problems with known analytical solutions must be reproduced within solver tolerance; patch tests for element formulations must pass.",
      "rationale": "Each code was exercised against NAFEMS benchmark problems for linear elastic structural analysis. Patch tests confirmed element formulations. All results converged within 0.5% of analytical reference values, satisfying required level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study must demonstrate that QoI changes less than 2% between successive refinements; Richardson extrapolation GCI < 5%.",
      "rationale": "Three mesh densities were evaluated (coarse ~180k elements, medium ~420k, fine ~910k). Richardson extrapolation yielded GCI values of 1.8%, 2.3%, and 1.5% for stiffness, yield force, and force-at-40mm respectively. Medium mesh adopted for production runs; discretization error contribution to combined uncertainty budget documented."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Residual norms must fall below 1e-6 for all load steps; contact penetration must remain below 0.01 mm.",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear static analyses used Newton-Raphson iteration with force residual tolerance 1e-7. Maximum contact penetration across all 11 construct replications was 0.004 mm. Solver logs reviewed by independent analyst; no convergence anomalies detected."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented simulation plan and independent review of model setup by a second analyst before result extraction.",
      "rationale": "A pre-analysis simulation plan was approved prior to model execution. An independent senior analyst reviewed boundary condition assignments, material property inputs, and contact definitions against the approved plan. No discrepancies were identified. Required level 2 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Physics represented (linear elastic with contact) must be justified as adequate for the QoIs of interest; sensitivity analysis must show model form assumptions do not dominate uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic continuum mechanics with frictional contact is well-established for metallic implant stiffness and yield-point prediction under quasi-static loading. Sensitivity analysis showed material nonlinearity (bilinear isotropic hardening) altered yield force prediction by <3%, within the combined uncertainty budget. Model form judged adequate for required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from coupon testing of the same lot material; geometric inputs derived from CMM measurements of actual test constructs; uncertainty characterised.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V material properties (E, yield stress, UTS) obtained from dog-bone coupon tests (N=6, same lot as screw blanks). Construct geometry confirmed via CMM to within ±0.02 mm. Input uncertainty propagated through Latin Hypercube sampling (n=500). Combined input uncertainty contribution to QoI uncertainty: 4.1% (stiffness), 5.3% (yield force), 4.8% (force-at-40mm)."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 constructs tested; samples traceable to same design and manufacturing lot as modelled geometry; inter-laboratory consistency demonstrated.",
      "rationale": "N=11 constructs tested across two independent laboratories (FDA CDRH biomechanics lab and DePuy Synthes test facility). All constructs manufactured from the same design revision and material lot. Inter-laboratory coefficient of variation for stiffness was 3.2%, confirming consistency. Sample traceability documented via lot certificates."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Multiple loading configurations or load levels tested to characterise model behaviour across the COU envelope; required level 3 demands at least two distinct test conditions.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted under a single ASTM F1717 standard load configuration (static compression-bending at 5 mm/min). No additional load levels or construct orientations were evaluated. Achieved level 2 (single condition, two labs) does not meet required level 3. This gap is noted as a known limitation of the current dataset; the overall assessment remains Accepted because all other factors meet or exceed required levels and the single condition directly mirrors the intended COU loading."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model input parameters must be demonstrably equivalent to experimental specimen parameters; traceability matrix linking CMM measurements to FEA geometry required.",
      "rationale": "A traceability matrix maps each FEA geometric parameter to the corresponding CMM measurement for every construct. Material properties assigned per coupon test results for the same lot. Friction coefficients for Ti-Ti contact surfaces set to 0.3 per published literature and confirmed by sensitivity analysis to have <2% influence on QoIs. Full equivalency documented in the simulation report."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric E/uval < 1.96 and percentage difference < 10% for all three QoIs.",
      "rationale": "For all three QoIs, E/uval values were: stiffness 0.84, yield force 1.21, force-at-40mm 1.07 — all below the 1.96 threshold. Percentage differences were 3.1%, 5.8%, and 4.4% respectively, all below 10%. Pre-specified acceptance criteria met for all QoIs across both laboratories."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force-at-40mm) must be directly linked to the clinical and regulatory decision context; justification documented.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness is a primary biomechanical performance metric for spinal fixation devices. Yield force and force-at-40mm directly correspond to ASTM F1717 regulatory acceptance thresholds. All three QoIs are referenced in the FDA guidance for 510(k) submissions for pedicle screw systems, confirming direct relevance to the COU decision."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation scenario (geometry, loading, material, boundary conditions) must correspond directly to the COU scenario with no unexplained gaps.",
      "rationale": "The validation scenario replicates the COU scenario in full: same 7.5 mm non-cannulated pedicle screw geometry, same Ti-6Al-4V material, same ASTM F1717 test fixture and loading protocol, same QoIs. No extrapolation beyond the validated scenario is required for the COU decision. Relevance is rated at the highest applicable level for the model risk level."
    }
