    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels. The single deficiency — Test conditions achieving level 2 against a required level 3 — is acknowledged; however, the ASTM F1717 standard mandates the single-condition protocol, and all quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96, QoI difference < 10%) are satisfied across both laboratories. The overall credibility evidence is judged sufficient to support the intended regulatory submission decision. Package integrity is recorded via SHA-256 hash.",
